                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I presume the shard bag would be just like an ammo pouch. Frankly I'd only use it if it were about double the size of my regular bags (10 slotters at the moment). I regularly start destroying shards at the end of a long expedition or instance run so I can carry more loot (and then am gimped until I can go shard farming again).
<br />

<br />
The only real news here is that eventually we'll be able to get shards in PvP. It had better be as easy as in PvE though--I hear casting a "leash" spell is a great way to attract unwanted attention in a large battle. Shards get created and used pretty steadily in PvE, and I don't hear anyone saying warlocks are overpowered as a result.
<br />

<br />
I'm just not seeing how shards really balance anything. Most of the time it's timers keeping me from using them faster, not lack of mobs to drain. The only times they're really an issue is if I'm trying to fight mobs well above my level so I might use a couple of shards per fight, or if I'm fighting greys (to help a friend with a quest for example). Mostly they just give me headaches trying to make room for shards, tradeskill stuff, and loot.
<br />

<br />
But the real complaint about this update is that ignores the issues people really care about. I'm not high enough to have seen it for myself, but it's not infernals breaking enslave on their own that people complain about. It's having them dispelled and then tapped so they can't be reenslaved but still want to kill you. That and the fact that an ordinary, risk-free hunter pet will kill an infernal.
<br />

<br />
Personally my only complaint is that I don't feel like I contribute as much to an instance group as I'd like. Soulstones are great, but that's like being invited into a group to cast KEI. Maybe that's just me not having done enough instances though. Or it could be my affliction build.
<br />

<br />
I've got mixed feelings on this...on the one hand this reminds me a bit too much of SOE communication about enchanter issues. On the other hand I'm still having a lot of fun playing my warlock, so I'm not going to get upset about it yet.
<br />

<br />
Teremar Talfirien</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
