                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">If so they don't do a very good job of it.
<br />

<br />
If I'm fighting mobs around my level, shards do not limit my spellcasting whatsoever. It's not like I'm going to use more than one shard per mob. The only things shards do is take up space in my bags, since I need a reserve for other situations.
<br />

<br />
If I'm fighting greys (and I had to kill a lot of them earlier today to get my felhunter quest done) I have no shards coming in. But I don't have to use healthstones to survive either, so it's not really a problem.
<br />

<br />
It's when I'm fighting really tough mobs where I might lose a pet and use a healthstone before I kill one (and can't always finish with Soul Drain) that it's an issue. Not using up shards isn't really an option--I have to go all out or I lose. So my shard supply basically dictates how long I can go at them before I have to quit and go farm shards for a while.
<br />

<br />
I haven't done much PvP, but right now it's the worst of both worlds--no shards coming in, but tough opponents that pretty much require you to use shards.
<br />

<br />
I don't see how this makes things harder or more interesting. It's just an annoyance. But on a scale of one to ten, I'd rate the importance of this issue at about a four.
<br />

<br />
Teremar Talfirien
<br />

<br />
Edit: typo</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Teremar on Thu Feb 10, 2005 9:31 am; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
                        </tr>
